135 (d) The initial term for appointments shall be two years and shall be made by
136 December 1, 2025. All subsequent terms shall be for four years. Any vacancies that occur
137 prior to the end of a term shall be filled by appointment in the same manner as the original
138 appointment and shall be for the remainder of the unexpired term. Members shall be
139 eligible for reappointment so long as they continue to meet the requirements for
140 appointment. A member who becomes ineligible for reappointment to his or her seat
141 during his or her term may serve out the remainder of such term.
142 (e) The board may appoint additional persons, such as representatives from educational
143 institutions and nongovernmental organizations with specific expertise in disaster
144 resilience, to serve in an advisory role to the board. Such advisers shall be nonvoting and
145 shall not be counted toward a quorum.
146 (f) A majority of the board shall constitute a quorum, and the concurrence of a majority
147 shall be required for the determination of any matter within its duties.
